Class ExtractorCell

java.lang.Object
neupaths.api.Cell
neupaths.api.ExtractorCell
public class ExtractorCell extends Cell
NeuPaths cell type for extracting stimuli from a NeuPaths cell system.

  • Constructor Details

    • ExtractorCell

      public ExtractorCell(String name, String synapseName, ExtractorSubscriptionSpec subscription, byte[] cryptoKey)
      Allocates a new ExtractorCell object.
      Parameters:
      name - The cell's name at runtime. This name should be unique across the entire cell system.
      synapseName - The synapse this cell listens on or connects to.
      subscription - The subscription this cell advertises.
      cryptoKey - The stimulus encryption key. Specify null to disable encryption using a user-specified key. If disabled, the stimuli will still be encrypted as part of NeuPaths protocol encryption.

  • Method Details

    • extract

      public final <T extends Stimulus> T extract()
      Extracts the next available stimulus from the cell system. This method blocks until a stimulus matching the subscription arrives.
      Type Parameters:
      T - A stimulus type derived from Stimulus.
      Returns:
      The stimulus.

    • extract

      public final <T extends Stimulus> T extract(long timeoutSecs)
      Extracts the next available stimulus from the cell system. This method blocks until a stimulus matching the subscription arrives or the timeout expires.
      Type Parameters:
      T - A stimulus type derived from Stimulus.
      Parameters:
      timeoutSecs - The number of seconds to wait for a stimulus.
      Returns:
      The stimulus or null if request expired.

    • extractFromTransaction

      public final <T extends Stimulus> T extractFromTransaction(UUID transactionID)
      Extracts the next available stimulus in the specified transaction from the cell system. This method blocks until a stimulus matching the subscription and transaction arrives.
      Type Parameters:
      T - A stimulus type derived from Stimulus.
      Parameters:
      transactionID - The transaction to wait for.
      Returns:
      The stimulus.

    • extractFromTransaction

      public final <T extends Stimulus> T extractFromTransaction(UUID transactionID, long timeoutSecs)
      Extracts the next available stimulus in the specified transaction from the cell system. This method blocks until a stimulus matching the subscription and transaction arrives or the timeout expires.
      Type Parameters:
      T - A stimulus type derived from Stimulus.
      Parameters:
      transactionID - The transaction to wait for.
      timeoutSecs - The number of seconds to wait for a stimulus.
      Returns:
      The stimulus or null if request expired.

    • setTransactionHistoryWindow

      public void setTransactionHistoryWindow(long millisecs)
      Sets the transaction history window duration.

      The default is 60000 milliseconds (1 minute.) The minimum is 250 milliseconds. Values less than the minimum will be automatically changed to the minimum value.

      Parameters:
      millisecs - The window of time maintained in the transaction history.
